in html, how can I make popup footnotes?

To create popup footnotes in HTML, you can use the "tooltip" feature. Here's how:

Wrap the footnote text in a span element with a class name. For example, <span class="footnote">This is the footnote text.</span>

Create a superscript number in the text where you want the footnote to appear. For example, <sup>1</sup>

Add an event listener to the superscript number using JavaScript or jQuery. Here's an example using jQuery:

[javascript]
$(document).ready(function() {
  $("sup").hover(function() {
    var footnoteText = $(this).next(".footnote").html();
    $(this).append('<span class="tooltip">' + footnoteText + '</span>');
  }, function() {
    $(this).find(".tooltip").remove();
  });
});


[css]
.tooltip {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  background-color: #fff;
  border: 1px solid #000;
  padding: 5px;
  z-index: 999;
}

This code will create a tooltip that appears when the user hovers over the superscript number. The tooltip will contain the footnote text. When the user moves their mouse away from the superscript number, the tooltip will disappear.






